🫶 09.03 🫶
Last night was awesome, missing a few but honestly I couldn't have asked for a better way to end my year. Here's to another year of growing closer to God, acquiring wisdom, expressing love, and maintaining health. I never thought I'd be here in life, let alone being alive. Thanks to Gods grace and the village of angels that surround me daily, I've grown into the person I knew was inside 🫶💕

I love you all
#birthday #birthdaygirl #love #godisgood #friends #family #superwheels #rollerskating

Joshua 1:9 always reminds me of my strength through God. He is always there, no matter what. Give up your sadness, anxiety, and fear. Surrender it all to Jesus Christ.

People will argue, "why does God let bad things happen?" Because His children aren't of this world. 

“This is how we know who the children of God are and who the children of the devil are: Anyone who does not do what is right is not God’s child, nor is anyone who does not love their brother and sister.”
‭‭1 John‬ ‭3‬:‭10‬ ‭NIV‬‬ 

I did not understand this before I was saved. I would respond with passive, aggressive remarks.

But now I understand. We all have the choice to be children of God. He's waiting open armed, but we have to make the choice to accept.

#godisgood #jesuschrist #ourking #bekind #love #god

🎃 October Dump 💃 
I've taken a break from posting on my feed bc I don't like to just throw content up for the sake of likes. I like to posts with intenton. This last month I've been adjusting to a lot of new necessary changes I've had to make in order to be in a better place in the future. 

Here is our October of memories. I'm forever in debt to the Lord for many reasons, but for my daughter I'd give anything to have my life replay exactly as it has. She is my wisdom, but blessing from God that I didn't deserve. I love you all. Thank you for being my fam 🫶

✨Noche.Buena 12.24.2023✨
Life is complex, sometimes we let everyday routine wear down the real meaning of it all. The present moment is exactly that, a present. 

Its a surreal experience losing Abuela. Especially how fast it happened. The more I've spoken to God about it, the more at peace I am.  That he's taken her with grace and mercy. 

Now it's our responsibility to carry on the legacy left behind. What we do today, shapes our tomorrow. Keeping tradition alive 🫶🤍

“Brothers and sisters, we do not want you to be uninformed about those who sleep in death, so that you do not grieve like the rest of mankind, who have no hope. For we believe that Jesus died and rose again, and so we believe that God will bring with Jesus those who have fallen asleep in him. According to the Lord’s word, we tell you that we who are still alive, who are left until the coming of the Lord, will certainly not precede those who have fallen asleep. For the Lord himself will come down from heaven, with a loud command, with the voice of the archangel and with the trumpet call of God, and the dead in Christ will rise first.”
‭‭1 Thessalonians‬ ‭4‬:‭13‬-‭16‬ ‭NIV‬‬

✨December 25, 2023 🎄✨🎁
The only way to anything, is through Jesus Christ. 
I've gained peace after releasing my life to Him. How do I get through the daily pain of missing someone- Speaking to the Lord and having faith that one day we'll meet again 🤍

We think we have all of the control, but the truth is GOD is the one with the directions. We are trying to figure out the map, the only way to crack the code is to get the know JESUS CHRIST. Surrender to him and he'll guide you like a Sheppard to his sheep.

Last weekend of 2023 🫶 
🚜 @pintofarm
